<pdd-reason>Applies discount codes to a shopping cart subtotal.</pdd-reason>

% Write `pdd/discount.py`.

% Requirements
- Provide `apply_discount(subtotal: float, code: str) -> float`.
- A `PERCENT10` code subtracts 10% of the subtotal.
- A `FLAT5` code subtracts a flat 5.00 (never below 0.00).
- An unknown code raises `ValueError`.
- A negative subtotal raises `ValueError`.

<contract_rules>
R301 - Percent discount
`apply_discount` MUST return `subtotal * 0.9` for code "PERCENT10".

R302 - Flat discount floor
`apply_discount` MUST return `max(0.0, subtotal - 5.0)` for code "FLAT5".

R303 - Unknown code
`apply_discount` MUST raise ValueError for any code other than the two
documented codes.

R304 - Negative subtotal
`apply_discount` MUST raise ValueError when `subtotal < 0`.
</contract_rules>

% User Stories
- As a shopper, when I enter PERCENT10 on a $50 cart, I am charged $45.
- As a shopper, when I enter an expired code, I see an error.

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/discount.py`
